{
  "stem": "10768.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "Otwock was, before the war, was like a, a resort place.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "It had beautiful buildings.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And they were resort place that a lot of people from Warsaw came there to rest.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "So we were given already buildings.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "This was the first time since I left, let's say, Chardjou that we were able to take a shower-- a regular shower.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "There we had buildings, which one was operating room number one, operating room number three-- number two, three.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "We had a few buildings.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And we had one room, which was like a dressing room-- a dressing room to dress the wounds from the people, from the patients-- and a room where we were supposed to bring in everybody who was admitted to us.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "The admitting procedure was quite difficult.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "Let's see, at that time already, since I knew Russian and Polish, and I knew German-- and of course Yiddish also.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "Yiddish was not a language that was needed there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "But these languages helped in reading the diagnosis.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "And after reading the diagnosis from wherever place our sick people or injured people were sent to us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "After reading the original diagnosis, after seeing their name and from where they came-- from what kind of military unit, there we had to write up some papers, take away their-- they call it [NON-ENGLISH] because they were getting so much bread and so much sugar.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "From there, at that time I was working in what they call [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "This is what, what was meant-- I, I segregate the people in which department they should go-- in the first surgery department, in the second surgery department, in a therapeutic department, in an infectious disease department.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "We had a lot of people, a lot of soldiers with gonorrhea.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "We had people with syphilis.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
